Use the correct username for your AMI and your private key to log in.

Open Windows Terminal (PowerShell or Command Prompt)

For Amazon Linux:

ssh -i C:\Users\YourUser\.ssh\soc-ec2-key.pem ec2-user@<PUBLIC_IP>

For Ubuntu:

ssh -i C:\Users\YourUser\.ssh\soc-ec2-key.pem ubuntu@<PUBLIC_IP>

For Debian (often):

ssh -i C:\Users\YourUser\.ssh\soc-ec2-key.pem admin@<PUBLIC_IP> or root@<PUBLIC_IP>

Type yes when asked to confirm the host fingerprint
